  Key Technical Challenges You Solved

  1. rate()[5m] smoothing — Prometheus averages metrics over 5-minute windows, which hides short CPU spikes. You handled this by adjusting thresholds and  
  using yes > /dev/null to generate realistic CPU workloads in test scenarios.
  2. Small container memory fluctuations — Tiny containers (< 1MB memory) show percentage swings that look like "memory decreasing." Fixed by adding an    
  absolute threshold (1MB) alongside the percentage check.
  3. Network timestamp misalignment — Prometheus scrapes network RX and TX at slightly different timestamps. Adding the two pandas Series produced NaN     
  values. Fixed by using .values to bypass index alignment.
  4. Single-rule detection dilution — When only one rule detects a zombie, the weighted average alone is too low. The boost formula + 0.3 × max_rule solves
   this.

